    Paragraph: 19
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Let It Be, Leave It Alone
---
Cloud Chief was traveling east and had passed the branches of the
Fu-yao when he suddenly came upon Big Concealment. Big Concealment at
the moment was amusing himself by slapping his thighs and hopping
around like a sparrow. When Cloud Chief saw this, he stopped in
bewilderment, stood dead still in his tracks, and said, "Old gentleman,
who are you? What is this you're doing?"
